Preheat your oven to 200°C and put the #kettle{} on to boil. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into roughly ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and cut into ½cm slices. Trim the tops from the @green beans{1} and chop into 2cm lengths. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the @lemon{1}, then cut it into wedges.

Pour the boiling @water{400%ml} into a #measuring jug{} and add the @chicken stock pot{1} and @saffron{1%pinch}. Stir to dissolve. Chop the @British chicken thighs{2} into 2cm chunks. Add some @olive oil{1%tbsp} to a large #ovenproof saucepan{} on medium-high heat (if you don't have one, transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later). Fry the chicken until browned, turning regularly, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add the onion, and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the pepper, green beans, garlic and @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp} to the pan. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @risotto rice{175%g}. Stir to coat in oil and spices. Add the stock and bring the mixture to the boil (then transfer to an ovenproof dish if necessary). Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and cook on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: Check after 20 mins to see if the rice is cooked and the liquid absorbed.

Slice each @sea bream fillets{2} into three pieces. Place in a #mixing bowl{} and add half the lemon zest, a glug of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{}. Rub the flavours into the skin and flesh of the fish, then set aside. In a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining lemon zest with the parsley and stir in the olive oil. Squeeze in the juice of half the lemon wedges. Season with salt to taste and set aside.

~{10%minutes} into the rice's cooking time, put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, carefully lay in the sea bream pieces, skin-side down. Cook until the edges begin to brown and the skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes} - don't move them during this time, then turn and cook for ~{2%minutes} on the other side.

> TIP: The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque.

Transfer the fish to some #kitchen paper{} to absorb any excess oil.

When the rice is ready, remove it from your oven and leave to cool for a few minutes. Taste and season with salt and @ground black pepper{1%tsp} if needed. Share between your bowls, top with the sea bream and spoon over the parsley and lemon oil. Serve with the remaining lemon wedges to squeeze over at the table. Enjoy!